text: Conecuh County is a county of the U.S. state of Alabama. Its name is believed to be derived from a Creek Indian term meaning "land of cane." As of the 2020 census, 11,597 people lived there. Its county seat is Evergreen, Alabama. ==Geography== According to the United States Census Bureau, the county has a total area of , of which is land and (0.3%) is water. ===Major highways=== * Interstate 65 * U.S. Highway 31 * U.S. Highway 84 * State Route 41 * State Route 83 ===Adjacent counties=== * Butler County (northeast) * Covington County (southeast) * Escambia County (south) * Monroe County (northwest) == Cities and towns == * Castleberry * Evergreen * McKenzie (part - part of McKenzie is in Butler County) * Repton ==References== Category:Alabama counties Category:1818 establishments in Alabama Territory
